    <body>
        <outline text="Prerequisites.">
            <outline text="An understanding of basic secret sharing techniques, including the Shamir Secret Sharing scheme. "/>
            <outline text="The app binary is available [here](https://kingston.box.com/s/zig6g56qb57t15krctb6zu7ype8k4pcs)."/>
            <outline text="The [corresponding documentation](https://kingston.box.com/s/rob2imh7r5kjoqi6944m4vb3ogy2bjtf)."/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Aim.">
            <outline text="To illustrate applications of Secret Sharing."/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Covered Learning Outcomes.">
            <outline text="LO2, LO4"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Problem Description.">
            <outline text="Scenario.">
                <outline text="The main purpose of this mobile app is to educate others on the concept of Secret Sharing. To achieve this, the app will demonstrate the functions and data needed to perform splitting of secrets and recombining them together to form the secret again. In addition to this, the app will show a use case where one might want to implement this technology. This will help with understanding the pros and cons of implementing this technology in a real-world scenario."/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Solution.">
                <outline text="Download the mobile app and install it over on your Android phone, or using the newly available virtual machine BlissOS which simulates an Android device."/>
                <outline text="See whether you can get it to work, you will require a Google account if you want to properly secret splitting."/>
                <outline text="Read up on the documentation or ask your instructor, if anything is unclear. "/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Wrap-Up."/>
        </outline>
    </body>
</opml>
